# Input
```jsx
// Invalid - separate opacity utilities should use modifier syntax
<div class="bg-red-500 bg-opacity-50" />;
<div class="text-blue-600 text-opacity-75" />;
<div class="border-green-400 border-opacity-25" />;

```

# Diagnostics
```
invalid.jsx:2:12 lint/nursery/useTailwindColorOpacityModifier  FIXABLE  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  i Use the opacity modifier syntax instead of separate opacity utilities.
  
    1 │ // Invalid - separate opacity utilities should use modifier syntax
  > 2 │ <div class="bg-red-500 bg-opacity-50" />;
      │            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
    3 │ <div class="text-blue-600 text-opacity-75" />;
    4 │ <div class="border-green-400 border-opacity-25" />;
  
  i Transformations: `bg-red-500` + `bg-opacity-50` → `bg-red-500/50`
  
  i The opacity modifier syntax (e.g., bg-red-500/50) is more concise and the preferred approach in modern Tailwind CSS.
  
  i This rule belongs to the nursery group, which means it is not yet stable and may change in the future. Visit https://biomejs.dev/linter/#nursery for more information.
  
  i Safe fix: Use opacity modifier syntax
  
    1 1 │   // Invalid - separate opacity utilities should use modifier syntax
    2   │ - <div·class="bg-red-500·bg-opacity-50"·/>;
      2 │ + <div·class="bg-red-500/50"·/>;
    3 3 │   <div class="text-blue-600 text-opacity-75" />;
    4 4 │   <div class="border-green-400 border-opacity-25" />;
  

```

